# Use Mermaid Diagrams in Markdown

When creating or updating documentation or Markdown files, **always use Mermaid diagram syntax** for any visual diagrams, flowcharts, architecture diagrams, sequence diagrams, or state machines.

## Rules

- Use fenced `mermaid` code blocks for all diagrams
- Do NOT use ASCII art boxes, arrows, or table-based diagrams
- Choose the appropriate Mermaid diagram type for the content:
  - `flowchart` / `graph` for pipelines, data flows, architecture
  - `sequenceDiagram` for API call sequences, request/response flows
  - `stateDiagram-v2` for state machines, status transitions
  - `erDiagram` for database schemas
  - `gantt` for timelines, project phases

## Examples

```markdown
<!-- ❌ BAD: ASCII art diagram -->
┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐
│  Input   │───▶│ Process  │───▶│  Output  │
└──────────┘    └──────────┘    └──────────┘

<!-- ✅ GOOD: Mermaid diagram -->
```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[Input] --> B[Process] --> C[Output]
```

```markdown
<!-- ✅ GOOD: State diagram -->
```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> intake
    intake --> enriching
    enriching --> generating
    generating --> live
    generating --> error
```
